Woohoo, now that I'm home, that means I have my AP scores, finally! They were as follows:

Biology: 5 (Fat load of good that does me... My adviser won't let me use this credit)
World Lit: 3 (Oh well, I'll live)
BC Calc: 5 (Yay, that gets me out of Freshman math altogether)
Spanish: 3 (Meh, doesn't matter anyway)

So, I was happy with my scores. Here are my classes for next year... I think I have to sign up for more, though...

Chem 115: Fundamentals of Chemisty (Lecture and lab)
Biol 115: Principles of Biology (Honors)
Psyc 101: Introduction to Psychology

I also have to take the requisite freshman course that gets us used to college life, but I haven't been assigned to a class yet. I think I'm going to sign up for Statistics, fencing, and maybe another class to get more GEC credit. I'll know once the school year starts, though

Let's go Mountaineers!

My dad just informed me of this by E-mail, and I thought that you all should be made aware of it...

With all the sadness and trauma going on in the world at this moment, it is worth reflecting on the death of a very important person, which almost went unnoticed last week. Larry LaPrise, the man who wrote  "The Hokey Pokey" died peacefully at the age of 93.


The most traumatic part for his family was getting him into the coffin.


They put his left leg in.


And then the trouble started.

Well, this sure has been fun. I'm sitting in my room in Florida, hanging out. It's beautiful weather down here, with the usual afternoon storms that are quite entertaining. Anyway, before this, I was at orientation at WVU, which was quite interesting for many reasons.

1. I got my ID, meaning free admission to Ravinia!
2. I also got my schedule, and I don't have any classes after 12:30 (except for monday, when I think I have a class at 1:30)
3. I've decided to double major in Forensic Examination and Forensic Biology, plus get a minor in Spanish. Since I scored well on my placement exam for Spanish, it seems I can achieve the minimum 15 hours necessary in just one semester.
4. I got to stay in my dorm (Not my actual room, though, since that was on the girls' floor). I like it a lot.
5. I took pictures of the campus. I'll post them somewhere when I get home.
6. I met some really cool people, including a couple other direct admissions to the Forensics program.
7. I got a new cellphone, with a number local to Morgantown.
8. I'm gonna be a Mountaineer Maniac next year, meaning I'm guaranteed a free ticket to all football and Men's Basketball games.
And finally...
9. There's a sixteen lane bowling alley in the basement of the main student commons area. We got to bowl on it for free, and it was quite fun.

Other than that, this past week has been pretty uneventful. I'm gonna spend these next couple weeks hanging out on the racquetball courts or by the pool, methinks. It should prove to be a lot of fun, despite the fact that I won't be sharing that time with the one person I really would like to... Or any of my other friends for that matter. But oh well, in two-ish weeks, I'll be back home livin' it up :)

-Tom

Okay...some of these are pretty bad, but had to
send...couldn't help it!


     1. Two antennas met on a roof, fell in love   and
got married. The ceremony wasn't much, but the
reception was excellent. 

     2. A jumper cable walks into a bar. The bartender
says, "I'll serve you, but don't start anything." 

     3. Two peanuts walk into a bar and one was a
salted. 

     4. A dyslexic man walks into a bra. 

     5. A man walks into a bar with a slab of asphalt
under his arm and says:  "A beer please, and one for
the road." 

     6. Two cannibals are eating a clown. One says to
the other: "Does this taste funny to you?" 

     7. "Doc, I can't stop singing 'The Green, Green
Grass of Home.'" "That sounds like Tom Jones
Syndrome." "Is it common?"  Well, "It's Not  Unusual."


     8. Two cows are standing next to each other in a
field.. Daisy says to Dolly, "I was artificially
inseminated this morning." "I dont believe you," says
Dolly. "It's true,  no bull!" exclaims Daisy. 

     9. An invisible man marries an invisible woman.
The kids were nothing to look at either. 

    10. Deja Moo: The feeling that you've heard this
bull before. 

    11. I went to buy some camouflage trousers the
other day but I couldn't find any. 

    12. A man woke up in a hospital after a serious
accident. He shouted, "Doctor, doctor, I can't feel my
legs!" The doctor  replied, "I know you can't - I've
cut off your arms!" 

    13. I went to a seafood disco last week...and 
pulled a mussel. 

    14. What do you call a fish with no eyes? A  fsh. 

    15. Two fish swim into a concrete wall. The one
turns to the other and says "Dam!" 

    16. Two Eskimos sitting in a kayak were chilly, so
they lit a fire in the craft.  Unsurprisingly it sank,
proving once again that you can't have your kayak and
heat it too. 

    17. A group of chess enthusiasts checked into a
hotel and were standing in the lobby discussing their
recent tournament victories. After about an hour, the
manager came out of the office and asked them to
disperse. "But why," they asked, as they moved off.
"Because", he
    said, "I can't stand chess-nuts boasting in an
open foyer." 

    18. A woman has twins and gives them up for
adoption. One of them goes to a family in Egypt and is
named "Ahmal."  The other goes to a family in Spain;
they name him "Juan." Years later, Juan   sends a
picture of himself to his birth mother. Upon receiving
the picture, she
    tells her husband that she wishes she also had a
picture of Ahmal. Her husband responds, "They're
twins! If you've seen Juan, you've seen Ahmal." 

    19. Mahatma Gandhi, as you know, walked barefoot
most of the time, which produced an impressive set of
calluses on his feet. He also ate very little, which
made him rather frail and with his odd diet, he
suffered from bad breath. This made him. (Oh, man,
this is so bad, it's good. . .) A super calloused
fragile mystic hexed by halitosis. 
     20. And finally, there was the person who sent
twenty different puns to his friends, with the hope
that at least ten of the puns would make them laugh.  
  
    No pun in ten did.

Alright, so its official. After the college visits, I have made a decision. As of the Fall semester of 2006, I will be a Mountaineer. (That's West Virginia, for those who don't know) 

That's all. Comment if you wish

Well, I got more news from WVU. I got accepted for a rank 2 academic scholarship, meaning I get $18,000 over 8 semesters. It also means I have the opportunity to apply for a $32,000 scholarship. I'm excited. And I saw this in Scott's journal, and I thought I would give it a try...
Dear Santa...

Dear Santa,

This year I've been busy!

In October I gave a kidney (1000 points). In May I donated bone marrow to in a life-saving procedure (300 points). Last Tuesday I punched in the arm (-10 points). In March I gave a Dutch Oven (-10 points). In April I saved a busload of nuns in Angola (326 points).

Overall, I've been nice (1606 points). For Christmas I deserve a pony!

Sincerely,
ssj5pinfu

So I just realized that Scott answered my question, and being a man of my word, I will answer it.

I don't know when I will get the siren to go with the light and radio. Hopefully soon, but I wouldn't count on it :(

And for shits and giggles...


1. Reply with your name and I will write something random about you.
2. I will then tell you what song/movie reminds me of you.
3. I will pick a flavor of jello to wrestle with you in.
4. I will say something that only makes sense to you and me.
5. I will tell you my first memory of you.
6. I will tell you what color you remind me of.
7. I'll then ask you something that I've always wondered about you.
8. If I do this for you, you must post this on your LJ. (and be prepared to answer the question I ask in #7)

It seems like the cool thing to do. And when have I never given in to peer pressure?

-Tom

Well, I am home safe and sound, but no thanks to Dennis... Damned hurricane. At least I have my World Lit homework done! Now I just have Spanish... Damned Lutter. Oh well, I guess you can't dodge everything in life that is bad. 

But on a similar note, as my subject line may hint, I have a slight deviation in my plans.

1.) I will not be doing my ordeal this Wednesday. Instead, I will be doing it the 27, 28, and possibly 29 of July. Which brings me to my next point.

2.) Due to lack of adults, we will not be going to the U.P. for Boy Scout camp, which gives me that entire week off, except for the aforementioned dates.

I guess that is a plus. I am kinda disappointed, though. The UP is fun.

Well, time for me to eat dinner and unpack, and all the other fun things that one would associate with getting home from vacation. Adios!

-Tom

Well, I got home yesterday from camp Ma-Ka-Ja-Wan, which was mucho fun. Especially Friday. Why, you ask? Well, I will tell you why!

1.) It was the first. Happy 10 months, Nicole!
2.) I finished my Camping Merit Badge, finally.
3.) Because of number 2, I could have a Scoutmaster Conference with my SM, for my Life Scout rank.
4.) The staff was nice enough to supply Evan Williamson and Jive Monkey (Don't ask) for a Board of Review that day.
5.) I passed the BoR and I am now a Life Scout! 
6.) The Order of the Arrow fire was that night, and I got tapped out! Now I can do my ordeal at Fall Conclave and be a member of the OA!

And that was just one day! This past week, I was also hiking in the Porcupine Mountains. I got to camp alongside a creek, and on Lake Superior. We hiked a total of 25 miles over 2 half-days and a full day. It was great!

Well, that is all for now. I have a plane to catch to Florida, so I must be off. Then Drum Major camp, then up to the UP for another Boy Scout camp. This summer is going too fast! I hope you all have a good rest of the summer.

-Tom

Well, I guess this is it. Tomorrow, bright and early (6:30 to be exact) I leave for camp Ma-Ka-Ja-Wan in Wisconsin. There, I will be backpacking in the Porcupine Mountains. If you have never been there, I highly recommend it. But for now, I guess I must be off to bed. Goodnight and goodbye everyone.

-Tom

PS: Nicole, I love you. Very much

So, I finally figured out my extensive schedule for this summer... Ok, hold on to your hats!

June 26 - July 2: Camp Makajawan (Boy Scouts)
July 3 ~ July 15: Florida
July 17 - July 22: Drum Major Camp
July 23 - July 30: Camp Nirva (More Boy Scouts)
August 8 - August 19: Summer Band 

Now doesn't that sound like fun! I can't wait...

-Tom

The Keys to Your Heart

You are attracted to those who are unbridled, untrammeled, and free.
In love, you feel the most alive when your lover is creative and never lets you feel bored.
You'd like to your lover to think you are flexible and ready for anything!
You would be forced to break up with someone who was ruthless, cold-blooded, and sarcastic.
Your ideal relationship is open. Both of you can talk about everything... no secrets.
Your risk of cheating is zero. You care about society and morality. You would never break a commitment.
You think of marriage as something precious. You'll treasure marriage and treat it as sacred.
In this moment, you think of love as something you thirst for. You'll do anything for love, but you won't fall for it easily.
What Are The Keys To Your Heart?

Man, Rhetoric is the devil. 'Nuff said

-Tom

So, last night was a small social get-together for our school. Nothing big, just Prom.

Personally, I had a lot of fun. The music wasn't always that great, but I can live with it. Otherwise, the food was good, the company was good, and hanging out at Twans afterwards was fun

But now, I must get ready for we are going camping for the weekend (We being Nicole, Katelyn and I) which sounds like it will be a lot of fun.

Carpe Diem
-Tom

Well, it has been a while since I have updated, but this isn't an actual update. I will get around to doing that later. I just want to wish you all the most merry of Christmases and I hope you all have a happy new year too!

-Tom

Yeah, I stole the title from Nicole. But, For those of you who didn't notice, i wasn't in school today. And I won't be in school tomorrow. Thats because I went to the Doctor today, and the final diagnosis is *drumroll*

1.Ear infection
2.Throat infection
3.Sinus infection

Ok, it is another entry, and a look into the life of myself. Today is on the books. Here, I will pose the same question that is currently haunting my away message: why am I in such a bad mood? I'm angry, sad, and lazy, all at the same time. Could it be because of the revelations I have had in the past hour? I will let you decide.

Revelation #1: No one tells me anything. I know I have said this for a while, but it has just hit me that it is true. Take today for example. At my church, I run lights and sound during the services, along with a man named John. He usually does it, but when he isn't there, I do it. Apparently, John was not there this morning. Did anyone tell me this? Of course not. Of all the past 6 or 7 times he has not been there, no one has told me so. At least I was at the late service today, so I could do sound for that one. But still, my point stands. 

Revelation #2: Adam was right. It may sound weird, and funny, but Adam was right. But not about stage managers, he was right about me. His comment was "Stage managers are like carpet. You can walk all over them, and if they weren't there, you really wouldn't miss them." I have realized that this holds true for myself. This ties into #1 above. I can count on one hand the number of people that would be a little "off" if I didn't exist. Also, my only reason for existence is to be used (Not the good kind of used that Nicole implies.) It just really pisses me off. Is there a video that needs to be played? Give it to Tom, even if its just 5 fucking minutes beforehand. Need a spot filled in in the band? Ask Tom. Then, tell him what he is doing wrong. Need your computer fixed? Ask Tom. He knows what he is doing. 

Where is the point in which I just say "enough?" Am I past that already? Why me? Why isn't there anyone else that can do what I can? Why does everyone walk all over me? Why are you still reading this. Comment if you want. I bid you adieu.

-Tom

I think my title says it all. Sorry I haven't posted in a while. Between all my classes, I have had zero time for myself in quite a long time. So, I guess that since I have a spare moment, I could update all my faithful lj followers. So, I guess I will do from the end of last week.

3 days of straight testing in physics (Thats 6 periods, for those who don't know) That totally sucked. Weekend, had a Boy Scout campout, in which it rained. My tent was flooded. Yay. But then again, it gave me an excuse to make a big fire to dry out all the stuff that got wet. So, I guess it wasn't all bad. 

This week was a pain. I had a 150 point rhetoric paper due on monday. That was about it for this week. It was just the little things, though, that ate up my time. And on Wednesday, I had variety show tryouts. Every act that tried out made the variety show, except the one that I was in. Just because we couldn't swear, and without the swearing, it wasn't funny.

"So... That makes you a... gay robot."
"Yes. Thats right. I am a gay robot..."

"I bet we could pick up chicks in this thing. Like 2 or 3 chicks a piece."
"What are you going to do with 2 chicks?"
"Man, women are like voltron. The more you hook up, the better it gets."

THose were just some of the lines form our act. The act that got cut. But oh well, I will live. There is always next year. I think that is about it, except that THE QUARTER IS OVER! THERE IS A GOD! Sorry. I am just so happy that I only have 3 more quarters left of school this year. 

Tonight, I have a lock-in at my church, which sounds like it will be a ton of fun. I can't wait. So, until next time...

-Tom

Hey everyone. Sorry that I haven't posted in a while. I have been uber-busy. I have had a ton of homework, (Thanks a lot Ms. Glover), I was feeling a little sick, (No, it wasn't your fault Nicole), and I didn't really have anything to say. But, I guess I will update anyway. First of all, I am in a pretty good mood, because Nicole and I have officially been dating for about a month. Huzzah! That makes me so happy. The sad thing is, that I don't think I will get to see her this weekend. That kinda sucks, but then again, I have seen her for the past two weekends, so it isn't too bad. Our marching band had competition yesterday, and for all of you who don't know, we definitely sucked. It was a personal best, but we still got fourth place out of four bands. Oh well. Maybe we won't suck in Marengo next week. *Stifles laughter* And finally, the grand homework total for this weekend: Physics: book problems, a catapult lab, and a horsepower lab. Precalc: 2 book problems (not too bad). US History: a study guide for the Boston Massacre and the American Revolution. Spanish: Book problems, and a pesadilla, which I neglected to do for Friday, when it was due. Finally, I have a Rhetoric paper, which isn't due until Tuesday; but if I don't get it done now, it sure as hell won't get done Monday night. My life rules, doesn't it? Well, I need to go get ready for church. Hasta Luego, y'all. -Tom

I forgot to mention something. I would like to make other people happy. I have a Gmail account, and with that entails invites to other people. If you would like a Gmail account, drop me your name and E-mail address and I will get you an invite. If you don't know what Gmail is, go to http://gmail.google.com/gmail/help/about.html

Today was probably one of the best days I have had in a while. It started off crappy, because we got 3 extra homework problems because of some dicks who didn't clean up yesterday in physics. And, we had a quiz. Then, I totally bombed my Spanish oral. I remembered almost nothing of my script. Oh well. There were good points, though. Very good points.

A friend has asked me to build him a computer from scratch, and has allotted me a fairly generous budget with which to complete said device. It will be good.

My dad can't get into the BIOS of a laptop he is working on, so I may get to test out my password cracking skills.

I get to work on a broken computer and see if I can get it up and functioning again. Huzzah.

These, however, pale in comparison to the rest of the night. Nicole and I decided to go out to dinner, because this is probably the only free night that I will have in a while. We decided to go out for Thai food (hence the title). Needless to say, it was delicious. And spicy. That just made it more delicious. Then, we returned to her house and hung out for a while (2 hours?) and built a fire. Today was definitely good. I also got my bio turned in for the play. Possibly the shortest one I have written to date. Come see the play if you wanna know.

All in all, this was an amazing day. If anyone has anything else to add to this, feel free. 

-Tom

Yeah, I really need to update, so I shall. Things are pretty good. I am hating AP Physics, but that is to be expected. I also have a new E-mail address, for those who didn't know. If I haven't sent you the E-mail, or if you never had my E-mail address to start off, my new address is ssj5pinfu@gmail.com. Thats right, I have a Gmail account. That makes me so happy. Also, I have an E-mail for work if you want to send me stuff there. It doesn't really matter. That one is tlilly@kildeerpolice.com. So that is about it for now.

I will do this week, because I can. Monday was fun, because it was Early release, and we got to break pasta bridges in Physics. Good times. 

Today was pretty cool. I got "caught" with Nicole in the large ensemble room. What were we doing? Hacking the pop machine. Good times. And I got to sleep during 4th hour. That is always good. That is about all that I did today, except for licking Ben's precalc book. MM MM good. He told me to. That is all I have to say for myself. And finally, I went to marching band today, and PG was there. Man, I hate that school. Fervent passion. So, now, I am just procrastinating, because I have a rhetoric paper to write. I am off to do that, I guess. And keep the anonymous comments coming in the previous entry. They are interesting

-Tom

I would just like to express my personal thanks to all of you that extended a prayer or word of help to the Delaney family. I'm sure that they appreciate it too. Just wanted to say that.

Well, on to slightly happier things. It was a 3-day weekend. A very good 3-day weekend. I played D&D Friday night, and Chase was there. And I didn't even kill him. I am so proud of myself. Lol. I would never kill Chase. Even though he killed everyone else. Except me. Teehee... Anywho... Saturday, I did nothing, so it doesn't bear mentioning.

Sunday and today, my family and I held parties for my brother, as we never had a proper graduation party for him. So thats where I was all day yesterday and today. And, of course, I neglected my homework until about 5 tonight. So right now, I am perched in front of my computer, typing up a rhetoric paper. 

That is about all I did this fabulous 3-day weekend. That is sad, isn't it? My entire 3 day weekend was summed up in about 2 paragraphs. *tear*

-Tom

I would like to call everyone together for a single purpose. For those of you who know (knew) David Delaney, I have a request to make of you. His father was in a bad accident, and now he has very extensive injuries. It is not looking the best for him. I would just like to ask that everyone keep Rick in their hearts and in their prayers. For more information on what happened, go to www.livejournal.com/~steelthewarrior.

-Tom

Today was a good day. Why was it a good day? Well, let me tell you. First of all, I got a pretty good night's sleep, so I was feeling pretty good. Also, Nicole and I are officially dating now. That makes me happy. Also, we had set crew today, even though I couldn't stay for very long. Also, I started teaching confirmation today, which was a lot of fun. I got to show the entire class the lunchlady song by Adam Sandler and Chris Farley. So all in all, today was a very good day.

What nourishes me, destroys me,
-Tom

Life sucks. It is the first offical weekend of school, and I am already sick. And not like the sniffles sick, but like really sick. I have a fever, runny nose, upset stomach, etc. This means that doing the Physics lab is going to suck, because I have to stake out a traffic light. Really gonna suck. Does anyone have any suggestions on how I can feel better?

Quod me nutrit me destruit,
Tom

Well, I finally finished my rhetoric homework. And my AP Physics homework. I am finally finished with homework for this summer. That, my friends, is what we call a good thing. This weekend was pretty good. I got to spend the majority of yesterday with Nicole at V.A. just hangin out. The only bad thing was that I was feeling pretty bad this morning, as in sick. I had to go to church, though, and play my saxophone. That was not good. I got through it, though, and I am feeling marginally better. 

Next week is going to suck, yet rule at the same time. 

Reasons to suck:
     1.) look at my schedule
     2.) I have a locker down band hallway, which means I have to carry most of my books to my classes
     3.) I have to take the bus to school
     4.) I have to get this whole deal with Kaylie dealt with (small explanation below)
     

Reasons to rule:
     1.) I get to see people I haven't seen in a while
     2.) Jensen announces the musical
     3.) Set crew will supposedly start
     4.) I like most of my classes, it is just a huge load

Alright, here is an explanation of what is bugging me the most about next week. No, Kaylie and I are not technically dating as of now. We both made promises to each other that we would get back together at the beginning of next school year. Neither of us are apt at breaking promises, so we will uphold it. But Kaylie wants to know what will happen next year. The problem is, that nothing will happen next year. We will be dating again, but not for very long. Then, we will go our separate ways, and date other people. Her, probably the person she is dating now, and me, Nicole. 

I am just really angry at the way that our relationship ended, as it almost seems like a year of my social life was put down the drain, and that makes me very sad. Especially since Kay and I wanted to stay friends, but that is seeming doubtful as of now. This really sucks.

But then again, I guess I am almost looking forward to the final split, as it gives a sense of finality to our relationship. I am also looking forward to dating Nicole, as she is an amazing person. 

I guess that is all I have to say for now, and I just wanted to get that off my chest. Thank you to all that took the time to read this. And feel free to comment, positively or negatively.

Seize the day,
